# Monorepo single env file (repo root). Copy to `.env` and edit; never commit `.env`.
# Docker Compose and `scripts/docker-*.sh` read this path. Next + sync-api load it in dev (see below).
#
# =============================================================================
# Local development — web + Electron (what to have in mind)
# =============================================================================
#
# 1) Postgres — sync-api needs a reachable DATABASE_URL (default in code:
#    postgres://archon:archon@localhost:5432/archon_sync).
#    Typical: `docker compose --profile local-pg up -d postgres` then set DATABASE_URL below
#    to match (compose service hostname is `postgres` only inside Docker; on the host use
#    127.0.0.1:5432).
#
# 2) sync-api — `npm run sync-api` from repo root loads THIS file via apps/archon-sync-api.
#    Set JWT_SECRET (≥32 chars in production; dev can use the commented example).
#    PORT/HOST default to 4010 / 0.0.0.0. CORS defaults to permissive in dev so Next on :3000
#    can call sync-api on :4010.
#
# 3) Next web — `npm run dev:web` already sets NEXT_PUBLIC_ARCHON_WPN_USE_SYNC_API=1 and
#    NEXT_PUBLIC_ARCHON_WEB_BACKEND=sync-only. The client resolves the sync base to
#    http://127.0.0.1:4010/api/v1 in development when NEXT_PUBLIC_ARCHON_SYNC_API_URL is unset
#    (see packages/archon-platform resolve-sync-base). If you use the Docker gateway on :8080,
#    set NEXT_PUBLIC_ARCHON_SYNC_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8080/api/v1 (must include /api/v1).
#    For same-origin through nginx only: NEXT_PUBLIC_ARCHON_API_SAME_ORIGIN=1.
#
# 4) Electron — dev shell loads the Next app from ARCHON_WEB_DEV_URL (default http://127.0.0.1:3000),
#    so run `npm run dev:web` before or with `npm start` / `npm run electron`. File vault + IPC
#    do not need sync-api unless you use Cloud/sync features; optional vars below (RxDB mirror,
#    WPN-only file vault) apply to desktop only.
#
# =============================================================================
#
# --- Local npm (web + sync-api only; skips slow electron-rebuild on `npm install`) ---
# ARCHON_SKIP_ELECTRON_REBUILD=1
# Or once: `npm run install:web` / `npm run ci:web`. Electron: `npm run rebuild:electron`
#
# --- Electron ADR-016 (local RxDB mirror + optional renderer authority) ---
# Mirror: after each main `archon-workspace.json` persist, main pushes a debounced payload to the renderer;
# renderer hydrates RxDB snapshot + normalized WPN collections and can serve WPN reads via `getArchon()` overlay.
# ARCHON_LOCAL_RXDB_WPN=1
# Authority: main `WorkspaceStore.persist()` no-ops; renderer must call `Archon.flushWorkspaceRxdbMirrorToDisk(payload)`
# with the same v1 mirror shape (set in main process env when launching Electron).
# ARCHON_WORKSPACE_RXDB_AUTHORITY=1
#
# --- Docker / deploy (Compose interpolates ${VAR} from this file) ---
# Local Postgres container: omit when DATABASE_URL points at a remote DB; deploy defaults ARCHON_LOCAL_PG=0 then.
# Force compose Postgres anyway: ARCHON_LOCAL_PG=1
# ARCHON_LOCAL_PG=0
# DATABASE_URL=postgres://USER:PASS@HOST:5432/archon_sync
# JWT_SECRET=minimum-32-characters-for-production-signing-key
# ARCHON_GATEWAY_PORT=8080
# COMPOSE_PROJECT_NAME=archon
#
# --- sync-api (local `npm run sync-api` and defaults when not overridden by Compose) ---
# PORT=4010
# HOST=0.0.0.0
# DATABASE_URL=postgres://archon:archon@localhost:5432/archon_sync
# JWT_SECRET=change-me-minimum-32-characters-long
# CORS_ORIGIN=true
# --- Integration tests ---
# Point tests at a DIFFERENT database than your dev/prod `DATABASE_URL` — tests
# create throwaway schemas per run. Each test drops its schema in `finally`, but
# routing tests away from live data is still strongly recommended.
# ARCHON_TEST_DATABASE_URL=postgres://archon:archon@localhost:5432/archon_test
# When `ARCHON_TEST_DATABASE_URL` is unset, tests fall back to `DATABASE_URL`.
# Optional: smaller pg pool for serverless (also set automatically when VERCEL=1 on Next `/api/v1`).
# ARCHON_SYNC_API_SERVERLESS=1
# Optional: enable Fastify request logging when Next serves colocated `/api/v1` (off by default on Vercel).
# ARCHON_SYNC_API_VERBOSE=1
#
# --- Next web (`npm run dev:web` / Dockerfile.web build args; use NEXT_PUBLIC_* only) ---
# Sync client calls paths like `/auth/register` relative to this base — it must end with `/api/v1`
# (e.g. `http://127.0.0.1:4010/api/v1`). A bare `http://127.0.0.1:4010` yields 404 on `/auth/register`.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ARCHON_SYNC_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:4010/api/v1
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ARCHON_SYNC_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8080/api/v1
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ARCHON_WPN_USE_SYNC_API=1
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ARCHON_WEB_BACKEND=sync-only
# Force sync client to use the browser tab origin + /api/v1 (nginx gateway on same host).
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ARCHON_API_SAME_ORIGIN=1
# If unset: opening a non-loopback host (e.g. archon.studio) while NEXT_PUBLIC_ARCHON_SYNC_API_URL
# still points at 127.0.0.1/localhost is auto-corrected to same-origin /api/v1 in the client.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ARCHON_API_SAME_ORIGIN=0
# WebSocket base override for the realtime stack (notes-explorer push, Yjs).
# Set this when HTTP is same-origin (Next.js dev) but WS upgrades need a
# different host — Next's `app.inject()` HTTP handler can't return 101.
# Default behaviour: when SAME_ORIGIN=1 on a loopback page, the client
# auto-routes WS to ws://127.0.0.1:4010/api/v1 (the standalone Fastify
# sync-api). Override to point at a custom dev gateway, or to a wss:// URL
# that goes through nginx in production.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ARCHON_REALTIME_WS_URL=ws://127.0.0.1:4010/api/v1
#
# Next production metadata (canonical URL for OG / absolute links). Use your real public origin (no path).
# On Vercel, `VERCEL_URL` is a fallback at build time if unset (preview URLs); set SITE_URL for a stable canonical domain.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ARCHON_SITE_URL=https://your-app.example.com
#
# When web and sync-api share the same public host (one full-stack deploy, API under `/api/v1`):
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_ARCHON_SITE_URL=https://your-app.example.com
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_ARCHON_SYNC_API_URL=https://your-app.example.com/api/v1
# (`SITE_URL` = origin only; `SYNC_API_URL` = same host + `/api/v1` — required shape for the client.)
# CSP `connect-src` already includes `'self'`, so same-origin fetch works even if you omit SYNC and use
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ARCHON_API_SAME_ORIGIN=1 instead; setting both explicit URLs is still fine and documents intent.
#
# Optional: `1` serves `robots.txt` with disallow all (private / staging deployments — same env file can use same URLs above plus this).
# ARCHON_ROBOTS_NOINDEX=1
#
# --- Electron file vault (Track A legacy removal) ---
# When 1, `WorkspaceStore.persist` writes empty `legacy` and note IPC skips flat-store fallbacks (WPN-only on disk).
# ARCHON_WPN_ONLY_FILE_VAULT=1
# Set to 0 to skip automatic legacy flat tree → WPN migration on eligible project open (default: migrate when eligible).
# ARCHON_MIGRATE_LEGACY_FLAT_TO_WPN=0
#
# --- MCP: local loopback WPN bridge (Electron main; used by `packages/archon-mcp` with ARCHON_LOCAL_WPN_*) ---
# After opening a folder vault, main listens on 127.0.0.1 only. Token file: userData/archon-local-wpn-mcp.json
# ARCHON_WPN_LOCAL_HTTP=1
# Optional fixed port (default: ephemeral port chosen by OS).
# ARCHON_WPN_LOCAL_HTTP_PORT=41234
# Optional shared secret; if unset, a token is generated and stored next to the JSON file above.
# ARCHON_LOCAL_WPN_TOKEN=
#
# --- MCP: cloud session + browser device login (sync-api + `packages/archon-mcp`) ---
# Interactive cloud MCP: allow startup without ARCHON_ACCESS_TOKEN; use archon_login / archon_login_browser_* tools.
# ARCHON_MCP_CLOUD_SESSION=1
# Persist access+refresh under XDG_CONFIG_HOME or ~/.config/archon/mcp-cloud-auth.json (0600). Override path:
# ARCHON_MCP_AUTH_FILE=
# Optional AES-256-GCM wrapping (set a long random secret); file on disk is not plaintext when set.
# ARCHON_MCP_TOKEN_ENCRYPTION_KEY=
# Public origin for /mcp-auth links returned by POST /auth/mcp/device/start (production: your Next site URL).
# ARCHON_MCP_WEB_VERIFY_BASE=https://your-app.example.com
# How long each browser device-login request stays valid (ms). Default 30 days if unset.
# ARCHON_MCP_DEVICE_SESSION_TTL_MS=
# MCP access / refresh JWT lifetimes after device or password login (sync-api). Default 7d each if unset.
# ARCHON_JWT_MCP_ACCESS_EXPIRES=
# ARCHON_JWT_MCP_REFRESH_EXPIRES=
#
# --- Next: legacy /api/v1 proxy (local only in practice) ---
# Rare: rewrite /api/v1 to another origin (see apps/archon-web/next.config.mjs). Leave unset for Option B.
# ARCHON_HEADLESS_API_ORIGIN=http://127.0.0.1:9999
# On Vercel, HEADLESS is ignored unless you explicitly opt in (avoids 404 on new colocated routes):
# ARCHON_ALLOW_HEADLESS_REWRITE_ON_VERCEL=1

# --- Postgres (sync-api primary store) ---
# Local dev: bring up the containerized Postgres with `docker compose --profile local-pg up -d postgres`.
# DATABASE_URL is the canonical PG connection string consumed by `apps/archon-sync-api/src/pg.ts` pool.
# Defaults below match the local-pg compose service.
# DATABASE_URL=postgres://archon:archon@localhost:5432/archon_sync
# POSTGRES_USER=archon
# POSTGRES_PASSWORD=archon
# POSTGRES_DB=archon_sync
# ARCHON_POSTGRES_PORT=5432
# Integration tests should point at a separate PG database; tests drop the schema in `finally`.
# ARCHON_TEST_DATABASE_URL=postgres://archon:archon@localhost:5432/archon_test

# --- Realtime collab (Phase 1+) ---
# Master switch for the WebSocket realtime stack (POST /v1/realtime/ws-token,
# GET /v1/ws/space/:spaceId, Yjs body collab, structural-event fanout). Default
# true; set to 0 to disable in environments that haven't opted in yet.
# ARCHON_REALTIME_ENABLED=true
# Hocuspocus debounces snapshot writes per note. Lower = more PG writes; higher
# = more lag between an editor pause and the snapshot landing in PG. Default 2000ms.
# ARCHON_YJS_AUTOSAVE_DEBOUNCE_MS=2000
# How many recent yjs_state_updates rows the periodic compactor keeps per note.
# Default 200 — enough headroom for a long editing session, bounded log growth.
# ARCHON_YJS_COMPACT_KEEP=200
# How often the compactor runs, in ms. Default 300_000 (5 minutes).
# ARCHON_YJS_COMPACT_INTERVAL_MS=300000
# Redis pub/sub for cross-replica Yjs broadcast + awareness fanout. Required
# when running 2+ sync-api replicas (otherwise clients on different replicas
# split-brain). Single-replica deployments may leave it unset and Hocuspocus
# runs in-memory.
# REDIS_URL=redis://127.0.0.1:6379
# Stable identifier for THIS replica; the Redis extension uses it to filter
# self-broadcasts. Default: a random per-process UUID. Set to a stable name
# (e.g. pod name) so reconnects across rolling deploys behave predictably.
# ARCHON_REPLICA_ID=
# Namespace for Redis keys/channels. Default 'archon-yjs'. Bump it to isolate
# environments that share a Redis instance.
# ARCHON_YJS_REDIS_PREFIX=archon-yjs
# DoS hygiene: cap the number of concurrent Yjs WS sockets a single user can
# hold open. Sockets above the cap get closed with code 4429. Default 20.
# ARCHON_YJS_MAX_CONNS_PER_USER=20
# DoS hygiene: refuse to persist a Yjs document whose encoded state exceeds
# this byte budget. Default 5 MiB. Hits typically signal a runaway / abuse;
# raise it for legitimate large-doc cases after triage.
# ARCHON_YJS_MAX_DOC_BYTES=5242880
